about.summary:
The Output Viewer is designed to provide a framework for viewing arbitrary
output from diagnostics scripts, metrics, or any program that produces a
ton of different files that you want to look at it in an easy-to-use
fashion.

name: output_viewer
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "output_viewer" %}
{% set version = "1.3.0" %}
package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/esgf/{{ name }}/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5d91c424ce2f6a90297e882ef9b80585aa16e2665ddd10a8cbd25219cccf05bd

build:
    number: 1
    noarch: python
    script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - requests
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - requests

test:
   imports:
       - output_viewer

about:
  home: https://github.com/esgf/output_viewer
  summary: |
    The Output Viewer is designed to provide a framework for viewing arbitrary
    output from diagnostics scripts, metrics, or any program that produces a
    ton of different files that you want to look at it in an easy-to-use
    fashion.
  license: ESGF
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
    recipe-maintainers:
        - doutriaux1
        - zshaheen
        - xylar
